text:
"Looking to master Selenium framework from scratch , Python, JavaScript, Manual Testing,git, GitHub commands and more? You're in the right place!

With 10 years of QA experience, I'm here to share what I've learned (and continue to learn) through clear, straightforward tutorials.

Check out my YouTube channel: [QTomation](https://youtube.com/@qtomation) — completely free! Just bring your eagerness to learn and dedication to practice.

Open to suggestions and feedback.

Keep learning and evolving!"

Date & Time: September 28, 2024, at 7:00 PM
Link for registration :- https://lnkd.in/gTD8pMZm

Key Takeaways:
👉 Understanding the evolving landscape of CSR
👉Skills and qualifications necessary to thrive in the field
👉How to gain relevant experience and stand out as a CSR professional
👉Insights into opportunities in corporate and nonprofit partnerships
👉Networking and mentorship opportunities in CSR


About the Speaker:
Himani Gautam is a certified CSR Professional from The Institute of Company Secretaries of India, with a deep-rooted passion for social impact and sustainable development. She brings a wealth of experience, having previously worked with prestigious organizations like HCLFoundation and IICA India. A graduate in Development Studies from Azim Premji University, . Her journey from academia to impactful roles in corporate strategy serves as an inspiring example for those looking to build careers in the intersection of business and social good.

Don’t underestimate the power of SQL! ❌
  
If you're aiming for a career in Data domain, SQL isn’t just nice to have—it’s a must. 

Mastering SQL can be the difference between landing that dream role or failing. 

So, here's a breakdown of the KEY topics you should focus on to ace your technical interviews: 

1️⃣ SQL Basics  
   - SELECT statements, WHERE clauses, JOIN operations  
   - Data filtering, ordering, and grouping

2️⃣ Joins & Subqueries  
   - INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, FULL joins  
   - Mastering subqueries and their use in SELECT, WHERE, and FROM clauses

3️⃣ Data Aggregation & Grouping  
   - SUM, AVG, COUNT, MIN, MAX  
   - Using GROUP BY for better data insights

4️⃣ Indexes & Query Optimization  
   - How indexes work to speed up queries  
   - Techniques to make your SQL faster and scalable

5️⃣ Window Functions  
   - ROW_NUMBER(), RANK(), LEAD(), LAG()  
   - Advanced data analysis with PARTITION BY and ORDER BY

6️⃣ Common Table Expressions (CTEs)  
   - Temporary result sets with WITH clause  
   - Easier readability and query maintenance

7️⃣ Transactions & Data Integrity  
   - COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT for safe data changes  
   - Maintaining consistency across your database

8️⃣ Stored Procedures & Functions  
   - Automate tasks and reuse code with stored procedures  
   - Building custom functions to optimize workflows

9️⃣ Data Warehousing  
   - Understanding star schema, snowflake schema, fact & dimension tables  
   - Data modeling for efficient storage and retrieval

Focusing on these fundamentals will make your SQL game strong enough to impress any recruiter! 👍
